headline: 'Trump Home' reports, Novo warning, US–Iran tension lifts oil prices
summary: Market Domination host Josh Lipton takes a look at some of Tuesday's trending tickers and stories. Homebuilder stocks, including Lennar (LEN) and Taylor Morrison (TMHC), are climbing on reports that builders are working on a program for developing "Trump Homes." Novo Nordisk (NVO) stock is plunging after the company warned of a sales hit, due partially to increased competition. Oil (CL=F, BZ=F) prices are climbing as US–Iran tensions continue to escalate. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: US homebuilders working on plan to develop as many as 1 million ‘Trump Homes,' Bloomberg News reports
summary: Feb 3 (Reuters) - Homebuilders are working on a proposal to develop nearly a million "Trump Homes" that would address the U.S. affordability crisis, Bloomberg News reported on Tuesday.

headline: Homebuilding stocks gain on reports of "Trump Homes" plan
summary: Investing.com -- Homebuilding stocks surged Tuesday following a Bloomberg report that major builders are developing a plan for a "Trump Homes" program aimed at addressing the U.S. housing affordability crisis.

headline: Builders Push ‘Trump Homes’ to Win Backing for a Million Houses
summary: Lennar Corp. and Taylor Morrison Home Corp. are among the firms that have worked on the proposal, which calls for builders to sell entry-level homes into a pathway-to-ownership program funded by private investors, according to people familiar with the plan.  The private investors would bear any initial losses, said one of the people, who asked not to be named discussing the proposal.
